WEBVTT

00:02.102 --> 00:03.536
<i>[jazzy music]</i>

00:03.602 --> 00:05.071
<i>- ♪ Timmy's</i>
<i>still an average kid ♪</i>

00:05.138 --> 00:07.340
<i>♪ That no one understands ♪</i>

00:07.407 --> 00:09.442
<i>♪ Chloe's his new neighbor ♪</i>

00:09.509 --> 00:11.878
<i>♪ And she's ruining</i>
<i>all his plans ♪</i>

00:11.945 --> 00:12.912
- Ahh!

00:12.979 --> 00:13.913
<i>- ♪ All the wishes ♪</i>

00:13.980 --> 00:15.081
<i>♪ In the world ♪</i>

00:15.148 --> 00:17.250
<i>♪ So why should he care? ♪</i>

00:17.317 --> 00:19.552
<i>♪ Jorgen has reported</i>
<i>there's a fairy shortage ♪</i>

00:19.619 --> 00:21.755
<i>♪ So Timmy has to share ♪</i>

00:21.821 --> 00:24.758
<i>♪ His OddParents,</i>
<i>fairly OddParents ♪</i>

00:24.824 --> 00:27.260
- More than one?
- This should be fun!

00:27.327 --> 00:29.229
<i>- ♪ OddParents,</i>
<i>fairly OddParents ♪</i>

00:29.295 --> 00:32.232
<i>♪ Feather suit, nature boots,</i>
<i>laser shooting, rescue ♪</i>

00:32.298 --> 00:33.466
- World peace, kale treats,

00:33.533 --> 00:34.667
bunny feet, real neat!

00:34.734 --> 00:35.802
- What? No!
Leave me alone!

00:35.869 --> 00:38.438
My fairies!
Get your own!

00:38.505 --> 00:40.807
-<i> ♪ OddParents,</i>
<i>fairly OddParents ♪</i>

00:40.874 --> 00:42.776
<i>♪ Timmy, beware,</i>
<i>you'll have to share ♪</i>

00:42.842 --> 00:44.711
{\an8}<i>♪ Your fairly OddParents ♪</i>

00:44.778 --> 00:45.745
{\an8}- Yeah, right!

00:49.449 --> 00:52.385
<i>[lively music]</i>

00:52.452 --> 00:58.958
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:59.025 --> 01:03.563
[thunder rumbles]
[bat screeches]

01:03.630 --> 01:05.364
- Whoopie, Skull Beary!

01:05.432 --> 01:07.367
Time for another hideous day
of inflecting

01:07.434 --> 01:12.472
soul-crushing misery
on unsuspecting innocents.

01:12.539 --> 01:14.808
[screams]
What's happening to my

01:14.874 --> 01:17.277
beloved Anti-Fairy World?

01:17.343 --> 01:19.446
<i>The blood red skies</i>
<i>have turned to cheery blue.</i>

01:19.512 --> 01:21.448
<i>The greasy bats</i>
<i>have turned into songbirds.</i>

01:21.514 --> 01:22.882
[bird sings]

01:22.949 --> 01:24.417
<i>Flowers are blooming</i>
<i>in the jagged lava fields</i>

01:24.484 --> 01:26.052
<i>of my</i>
<i>wonderfully tortured youth.</i>

01:26.119 --> 01:28.655
Something has gone
terribly right.

01:28.721 --> 01:30.056
[zapping, popping]

01:33.326 --> 01:37.096
{\an1}- Foop, you've been summoned
by the Anti-Fairy Council.

01:37.163 --> 01:40.333
- The evil is being drained
from Anti-Fairy World,

01:40.400 --> 01:43.303
and it's all because
of the pure goodness

01:43.369 --> 01:47.340
and selflessness
of a single fairy godchild.

01:47.407 --> 01:51.411
- The fairy godchild in question
is one Chloe Carmichael.

01:51.478 --> 01:55.215
- Here's a little sample
of you-know-who in action.

01:56.816 --> 01:58.284
[crack]

02:01.588 --> 02:04.390
- Ah, yum, yum, yum, blah.
[bird squeaks]

02:06.626 --> 02:10.797
Be free, BFF.
The Best Flying Friend.

02:10.864 --> 02:14.234
[bird screeches]

02:14.300 --> 02:17.337
- This Chloe Carmichael,
she is a threat

02:17.403 --> 02:19.272
to everything
we stand for.

02:19.339 --> 02:22.709
Soon, her goodness
will drain all the bad mojo

02:22.775 --> 02:26.212
from our Anti-Fairy Wand,
and we'll be doomed

02:26.279 --> 02:30.283
to a world filled
with bunnies and lollipops.

02:30.350 --> 02:33.520
[electric zapping,
fire blazing]

02:33.586 --> 02:34.888
[explosion]

02:34.954 --> 02:38.758
- Foop, to save our world,
we need you to turn this

02:38.825 --> 02:40.460
girl from good to evil.

02:40.527 --> 02:41.594
Make her snap!

02:41.661 --> 02:42.595
- You picked the right

02:42.662 --> 02:44.097
square blue baby
for the job.

02:44.163 --> 02:46.666
I'm super irritating.
- You certainly are.

02:46.733 --> 02:48.535
- You're the worst.
- Everyone hates you.

02:48.601 --> 02:49.536
- You flatter me.

02:49.602 --> 02:50.904
To carry out my mission,

02:50.970 --> 02:53.139
I'm going to use this magical,
to die for,

02:53.206 --> 02:55.375
heart-shaped pendant
to transform myself into

02:55.441 --> 02:58.011
the most demoralizing creature
in the known universe,

02:58.077 --> 03:01.114
a popular,
middle school girl!

03:01.180 --> 03:04.584
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

03:07.220 --> 03:09.589
Check me out.
I am all that.

03:09.656 --> 03:11.224
I'm off in my
super cute shoes

03:11.291 --> 03:13.760
to, like, totally reclaim
my bad mojo.

03:13.826 --> 03:16.496
Evil hair flip.

03:16.563 --> 03:18.131
[pop]

03:22.468 --> 03:23.369
Oh!

03:23.436 --> 03:24.304
I've poofed into a urinal

03:24.370 --> 03:25.872
in the boy's bathroom.

03:25.939 --> 03:27.240
An awkward start,
to be sure,

03:27.307 --> 03:29.042
but no matter,
my magical pendant

03:29.108 --> 03:30.710
gives me the popular
girl power

03:30.777 --> 03:33.479
to cast a spell over everyone
so they think I'm awesome,

03:33.546 --> 03:37.083
no matter how ridiculous I look,
and how horribly I act.

03:37.150 --> 03:39.419
[strains, groans]
[thudding]

03:39.485 --> 03:47.961
[laughing]

03:48.027 --> 03:50.997
{\an8}- Wow, I think the new girl
is awesome,

03:51.064 --> 03:52.665
{\an8}no matter how ridiculous
she looks,

03:52.732 --> 03:54.334
{\an8}and how horribly she acts.

03:54.400 --> 03:55.702
That heavy,
porcelain urinal

03:55.768 --> 03:58.104
is an absolutely
to die for accessory.

03:58.171 --> 04:00.506
I wish I had one!

04:00.573 --> 04:02.108
[grunts]
- Whoa!

04:02.175 --> 04:03.443
Who is the new girl,

04:03.509 --> 04:05.912
besides the future
Mrs. Timmy Turner?

04:05.979 --> 04:07.947
- Oh, I want her
to like me so bad,

04:08.014 --> 04:09.716
I'll laugh at everything
she says,

04:09.782 --> 04:12.018
even though she hasn't said
anything yet.

04:12.085 --> 04:13.353
- Hi, everyone.

04:13.419 --> 04:16.555
I'm, um, ironic girl
named Angel.

04:16.623 --> 04:19.926
- Oh, yeah you are.
I love you, Angel.

04:19.993 --> 04:21.995
{\an3}I'd walk through fire
for you.

04:22.060 --> 04:23.529
{\an1}- You will,
now that you're

04:23.596 --> 04:24.397
under my spell.

04:24.464 --> 04:25.632
Um, I mean,

04:25.698 --> 04:27.934
{\an1}you're, like,
totally supes cute.

04:28.001 --> 04:30.370
- [laughs]
Su--hoo--hoo--hoo--

04:30.436 --> 04:31.838
- Oh, hi, everyone.

04:31.904 --> 04:33.006
I was hiding
behind my desk,

04:33.072 --> 04:34.507
hoping you'd all go away.

04:38.344 --> 04:40.380
Gah, who's the new girl?

04:40.446 --> 04:42.015
Besides my new bestie?

04:42.081 --> 04:43.883
- Now, with everyone
under my spell,

04:43.950 --> 04:48.688
it's time to bring down
she who must not be named.

04:48.755 --> 04:50.323
{\an3}- Sorry I'm late,
Mr. Crocker.

04:50.390 --> 04:52.792
I know you like Fiji apples,
so I rode my bike

04:52.859 --> 04:55.161
to Fiji to get you one.

04:55.228 --> 04:57.997
Greetings, new girl.
I'm Chloe Carmichael.

04:58.064 --> 04:59.666
{\an1}Just ask
if you need anything.

04:59.732 --> 05:02.802
{\an1}A tour of the school,
an extra pencil, a kidney.

05:02.869 --> 05:06.606
{\an3}- Ooh, you're good,
but soon you'll be bad.

05:06.673 --> 05:07.774
One bad apple.

05:07.840 --> 05:10.009
Like the one
you gave your teacher.

05:10.076 --> 05:14.647
{\an3}I, like, totally put Death Star
goscorpians in that apple.

05:14.714 --> 05:16.015
{\an1}[screams]

05:16.082 --> 05:17.450
[screams]

05:17.517 --> 05:19.686
{\an1}- I am so disappointed
in you, young lady.

05:19.752 --> 05:21.454
{\an1}You were the only student
in this class

05:21.521 --> 05:23.756
{\an1}who hadn't attacked me
with scorpions.

05:23.823 --> 05:25.124
To the principal with you.

05:25.191 --> 05:27.960
{\an1}Your perfect record
has been destroyed forever.

05:28.027 --> 05:29.262
{\an1}[sobs]
Mother.

05:29.328 --> 05:31.597
{\an3}- That's right,
you're angry.

05:31.664 --> 05:33.733
{\an3}Go with it.
Out with the good,

05:33.800 --> 05:35.034
in with the bad.

05:35.101 --> 05:37.837
Turn the fluffy bunnies
back into greasy bats!

05:37.904 --> 05:40.473
{\an3}I realize that sounded weird
out of context.

05:40.540 --> 05:43.042
- You are a strange
and tortured soul,

05:43.109 --> 05:45.878
but I forgive you.

05:45.945 --> 05:47.914
[growls]

05:47.980 --> 05:49.282
[claw snaps]
[groans]

05:49.348 --> 05:52.852
- I need a hall pass!
[grunts]

05:52.919 --> 05:54.187
- Thanks for helping me

05:54.253 --> 05:55.755
with my big clean up day
at the park, Timmy.

05:55.822 --> 05:57.757
{\an9}- Well, I heard Angel
might be here,

05:57.824 --> 05:59.358
but if she doesn't show,
I'm going to

05:59.425 --> 06:00.927
go look for her,
even if I have to

06:00.993 --> 06:02.762
walk over hot coals.

06:02.829 --> 06:03.963
She's my bae.

06:04.030 --> 06:07.066
{\an1}- Yeah, about Angel,
she seems to be,

06:07.133 --> 06:08.367
oh, how should I say this?

06:08.434 --> 06:10.069
Out to destroy me.

06:10.136 --> 06:11.204
Cosmo, Wanda,

06:11.270 --> 06:12.538
{\an1}what are you doing
in human form?

06:12.605 --> 06:13.506
- Duh!

06:13.573 --> 06:14.907
It makes it
a lot easier

06:14.974 --> 06:16.309
to lug around
this urinal.

06:16.375 --> 06:17.543
I Bedazzled it.

06:17.610 --> 06:18.745
- And I'm
in human form

06:18.811 --> 06:21.280
so I could dress
exactly like Angel,

06:21.347 --> 06:23.783
because I no longer have
any sense of self.

06:23.850 --> 06:27.086
{\an1}- Well, well, well,
if it isn't Chloe Carmichael.

06:27.153 --> 06:30.323
Hi! I've come to
Chloe's Clean up the Park Day--

06:30.389 --> 06:31.691
to ruin it!

06:31.758 --> 06:33.459
{\an1}Because now,
instead of wasting their time

06:33.526 --> 06:34.994
{\an1}spearing rubbish
with a stick,

06:35.061 --> 06:36.129
{\an1}everyone will be
driving these

06:36.195 --> 06:37.597
{\an1}environmentally unfriendly
sport cars

06:37.663 --> 06:40.066
{\an1}I just bought with my
rich daddy's credit card.

06:40.133 --> 06:41.501
all: Hooray!

06:41.567 --> 06:42.802
- Yay!

06:42.869 --> 06:45.805
<i>[rock music]</i>

06:45.872 --> 06:53.813
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:55.047 --> 06:57.383
- Aw, I see you're frowning.

06:57.450 --> 07:01.387
Now, come on,
hate a little.

07:01.454 --> 07:02.822
- I don't believe in hate.

07:02.889 --> 07:05.725
I strongly dislike it,
but I don't hate it

07:05.792 --> 07:08.394
because as previously mentioned,
I don't believe in hate.

07:08.461 --> 07:11.497
- [retches] I just threw up
in my mouth a little,

07:11.564 --> 07:14.834
but I won't quit
until you turn to the dark side.

07:14.901 --> 07:17.770
- I try not to be judgy,
but you guys have been acting

07:17.837 --> 07:20.807
just a little bit peculiar
since Angel showed up.

07:20.873 --> 07:23.276
- I have no idea
what you're talking about.

07:23.342 --> 07:24.677
Hold on,
I have to adjust

07:24.744 --> 07:26.913
{\an3}the shoulder straps on my
bedazzled urinal.

07:26.979 --> 07:29.482
- And what about you, Timmy?
- Angel's going to be here.

07:29.549 --> 07:33.853
Do I look kissable today?
- [laughs]

07:33.920 --> 07:35.721
- What's so funny?
- Nothing.

07:35.788 --> 07:37.757
I'm practicing
for when Angel shows up--

07:37.824 --> 07:40.593
OMG, she's here!

07:40.660 --> 07:43.396
{\an3}- Well, Chloe and friends,
it's your lucky day,

07:43.462 --> 07:45.932
Angel's in the hizzy.

07:45.998 --> 07:47.600
[camera clicks]

07:47.667 --> 07:49.368
{\an3}Don't tag me in that post,
you loser.

07:49.435 --> 07:51.037
- She knows who I am!

07:51.103 --> 07:53.506
{\an3}- Now to deal with you,
Chloe Carmichael.

07:53.573 --> 07:55.641
{\an3}You pretend to be such
a goody two-shoes,

07:55.708 --> 07:57.610
{\an3}but you're really a baddy
no-shoes!

07:57.677 --> 08:01.581
- Well, nobody's perfect,
but I try extremely hard

08:01.647 --> 08:03.583
to be a friend to everyone,

08:03.649 --> 08:05.952
especially to Timmy,
Cosmo and Wanda.

08:06.018 --> 08:09.922
{\an3}- Oh, really?
Would a friend do this?

08:12.158 --> 08:13.259
[all gasp]

08:13.326 --> 08:15.127
{\an3}- I can't read.
Is it bad?

08:15.194 --> 08:16.429
- It's terrible.

08:16.495 --> 08:18.331
{\an1}It says, "Timmy, Cosmo,
and Wanda

08:18.397 --> 08:19.365
"are stupid dum dums.

08:19.432 --> 08:21.801
Signed, 'Klowie'"

08:21.868 --> 08:23.569
{\an1}- What?
I didn't write that.

08:23.636 --> 08:25.504
{\an1}I would never
call my friends dum dums,

08:25.571 --> 08:27.139
{\an1}or spell my name
with a "K"!

08:27.206 --> 08:30.576
{\an3}- Then how do you explain that
can of spray paint in your hand?

08:30.643 --> 08:31.878
- You just put it there!

08:31.944 --> 08:35.381
{\an1}Cosmo, Wanda, Timmy,
I would never insult you.

08:35.448 --> 08:36.816
I love you guys.

08:36.883 --> 08:39.018
{\an3}- Come on, new besties,
let's kick

08:39.085 --> 08:40.852
{\an3}baddy no-shoes
to the curb.

08:43.322 --> 08:46.959
{\an3}My prediction is that
Chloe will snap in three, two--

08:47.026 --> 08:50.863
- Bye, guys.
If you're happy, I'm happy.

08:50.930 --> 08:53.933
{\an3}- Oh, come on!
You are killing me.

08:54.000 --> 08:56.135
No one's that good!

08:56.202 --> 08:58.204
[cries]

08:58.271 --> 09:00.673
- Don't worry, Angel,
we're still your friends

09:00.740 --> 09:02.675
no matter
how horribly you act.

09:02.742 --> 09:05.344
{\an3}- Maybe a kiss
will make you feel better.

09:05.411 --> 09:08.547
[mwah]
- Ew, yuck!

09:08.614 --> 09:10.616
Get away!
You're not my friends.

09:10.683 --> 09:12.151
I despise you all.

09:12.218 --> 09:13.419
You, with your toilet back,

09:13.486 --> 09:15.121
and you with that
unbearable laugh.

09:15.187 --> 09:17.456
{\an1}- [laughs]
- [yells]

09:17.523 --> 09:20.159
{\an1}And you, Mister...
[smooches] Kissy Face.

09:20.226 --> 09:21.560
{\an1}I would never date
a nerd like you.

09:21.627 --> 09:23.329
I prefer bad boys.

09:23.396 --> 09:25.231
Ah, what am I saying?

09:25.298 --> 09:26.465
[all crying]

09:26.532 --> 09:27.633
- Listen up, girlie.

09:27.700 --> 09:30.202
{\an1}You can mess with me
all you want,

09:30.269 --> 09:32.271
but do not mess

09:32.338 --> 09:35.541
with my friends!

09:35.608 --> 09:36.742
[both grunt]

09:36.809 --> 09:38.077
[growls]

09:38.144 --> 09:39.078
Hi-ya!

09:39.145 --> 09:40.079
Achoo!

09:40.146 --> 09:43.449
Wah!

09:43.516 --> 09:46.752
Ooh, you make me so...

09:46.819 --> 09:48.854
angry!

09:48.921 --> 09:49.855
[smack]

09:52.058 --> 09:54.827
- Well, if I can't destroy you
emotionally,

09:54.894 --> 09:57.897
I might as well, you know,
just destroy you!

09:57.964 --> 09:58.898
Ha!

10:01.233 --> 10:03.536
[groans]

10:03.602 --> 10:07.139
[both grunting]

10:07.206 --> 10:08.140
[eagle screeches]

10:08.207 --> 10:09.241
BFF!

10:09.308 --> 10:11.410
I always knew you'd come back!

10:11.477 --> 10:12.678
- I must be slipping.

10:12.745 --> 10:15.181
I totes forgot about
the eagle thing.

10:15.247 --> 10:16.716
Ah!

10:21.587 --> 10:23.356
- What?
Foop?

10:23.422 --> 10:24.790
- You monster.

10:24.857 --> 10:27.560
What did you do with my
angel named Angel?

10:27.626 --> 10:29.061
Ha! Heavy urinal!

10:31.731 --> 10:33.766
- [shouts]
I kissed Foop!

10:33.833 --> 10:34.867
Ew! Why?

10:34.934 --> 10:37.236
[groaning]

10:37.303 --> 10:39.638
- I don't normally use salty
language,

10:39.705 --> 10:41.707
but what the holy heck is going
on here?

10:41.774 --> 10:44.577
- Your pukey goodness was
wrecking Anti-Fairy World,

10:44.643 --> 10:46.712
so I had to make you snap.

10:46.779 --> 10:49.382
Your fit of rage has no doubt
restored Anti-Fairy World

10:49.448 --> 10:51.550
to the hideous place
it once was.

10:51.617 --> 10:53.486
Evil hair flip.
Drops mic.

10:53.552 --> 10:55.087
Foop out.

10:55.154 --> 10:58.024
- Chloe, you saved us from
Foop's evil spell.

10:58.090 --> 10:59.458
- [groaning]

10:59.525 --> 11:01.127
I still don't have any idea
what's going on,

11:01.193 --> 11:02.661
but we're at the mall,

11:02.728 --> 11:04.730
so let's all get a corn dog
and a funnel cake.

11:08.634 --> 11:10.102
<i>[ominous music]</i>

11:10.169 --> 11:12.705
- Oh, nothing like the sight
of greasy bats

11:12.772 --> 11:14.807
swooping through
a blood red sky.

11:14.874 --> 11:16.742
Ooh, what's this?

11:16.809 --> 11:19.245
Must be a gift from
the Anti-Fairy Council.

11:19.311 --> 11:22.481
Maybe they signed me up for the
rotten fruit of the month club.

11:22.548 --> 11:24.350
There's a note!

11:24.417 --> 11:26.352
"I forgive you.

11:26.419 --> 11:28.387
Love, Chloe"?

11:28.454 --> 11:31.891
No!
No one's that good!

11:31.957 --> 11:35.828
[zapping]

11:35.895 --> 11:37.229
[shouts]

11:37.296 --> 11:39.932
Oh!
Stupid eagle.

11:55.347 --> 11:57.116
[school bell ringing]

11:57.183 --> 11:58.884
- Well, the school day is over,

11:58.951 --> 12:01.454
{\an1}but that doesn't mean
the learning has to stop.

12:01.520 --> 12:04.457
- That's exactly what it means,
Brain Hilda.

12:04.523 --> 12:06.525
- I'm going to ignore your
good-natured barb

12:06.592 --> 12:09.495
and go finish my extra, extra
credit report

12:09.562 --> 12:12.698
positing that aliens
do not exist.

12:12.765 --> 12:14.700
- What?
Yes!

12:14.767 --> 12:16.168
Awesome!

12:16.235 --> 12:18.237
- Wait, you're excited about
my report?

12:18.304 --> 12:20.039
- Couldn't care less.

12:20.106 --> 12:22.808
{\an3}I'm excited that you're finally
wrong about something.

12:22.875 --> 12:27.113
{\an3}Cosmo, cue the Chloe's wrong
celebration.

12:27.179 --> 12:28.314
[horn blares]

12:32.751 --> 12:34.954
Now sing the "Chloe's Wrong"
song.

12:35.020 --> 12:36.522
You do, Wanda!

12:36.589 --> 12:38.791
{\an1}- Well, I'm not sure I feel
comfortable

12:38.858 --> 12:40.793
singing the songs for--

12:40.860 --> 12:42.394
- Sing it!

12:42.461 --> 12:44.430
all: ♪ Chloe's wrong,
and I wrote this song ♪

12:44.497 --> 12:46.799
♪ To say Chloe's wrong ♪

12:46.866 --> 12:48.701
♪ Wrong, wrong, wrong ♪

12:48.767 --> 12:51.003
- ♪ Wrong, yeah ♪

12:51.070 --> 12:52.071
That felt great.

12:52.138 --> 12:54.173
Anyway, aliens do exist.

12:54.240 --> 12:56.108
I'm friends with one named
Mark Chang.

12:56.175 --> 12:57.443
He's from the Planet
Yugopotamia,

12:57.510 --> 12:59.345
and he lives
at the Dimmsdale dump

12:59.411 --> 13:00.846
and looks like a squid,

13:00.913 --> 13:02.314
but with his brain on
the outside of his body.

13:02.381 --> 13:04.617
Oh, and he's also a prince.

13:04.683 --> 13:05.985
- Of course he is.

13:06.051 --> 13:08.954
{\an1}And I'm the queen
of Planet Your-Full-Of-Bologna.

13:09.021 --> 13:12.591
- Wanda, poof us to the dump
and end the crazy.

13:16.462 --> 13:17.930
Prepare yourself, Chloe,

13:17.997 --> 13:21.400
or shall I call you,
"Wrongy Miss Wrongerstein"?

13:21.467 --> 13:23.602
You're about to see an alien.

13:23.669 --> 13:25.104
Dude!

13:25.171 --> 13:27.339
- Dude!
And dude and dudettes.

13:27.406 --> 13:28.841
What's up?

13:28.908 --> 13:31.677
Check out these wind chimes
I made from muffles

13:31.744 --> 13:33.612
and bedpans!

13:33.679 --> 13:34.547
[laughs]

13:34.613 --> 13:36.115
- Mark, my friend Chloe here

13:36.182 --> 13:38.117
doesn't believe in aliens.

13:38.184 --> 13:40.486
{\an1}- Only because they do
not exist.

13:40.553 --> 13:42.521
{\an1}- Mark really is an alien,
Chloe.

13:42.588 --> 13:45.758
{\an1}He's just in his human form
as Justin Jake Aston,

13:45.824 --> 13:49.328
{\an1}moody teen dream with three
first names.

13:49.395 --> 13:50.996
- Chloe accepts everybody,

13:51.063 --> 13:52.898
even if they're super weird.

13:52.965 --> 13:53.999
- He's right, I do,

13:54.066 --> 13:56.569
because what is weird anyway,

13:56.635 --> 14:01.040
{\an1}but a judgment borne from
fear-based sociological norms?

14:01.106 --> 14:03.175
- All right, those were words.

14:03.242 --> 14:06.045
- Just show her you're an alien!

14:06.111 --> 14:08.547
[warbling]

14:08.614 --> 14:09.815
- Ha!

14:09.882 --> 14:10.816
- [screams]

14:10.883 --> 14:12.051
{\an3}- [screams]

14:12.117 --> 14:13.385
I told you, Timmy.

14:13.452 --> 14:15.287
{\an3}It freaked out
the little dudette.

14:15.354 --> 14:16.956
- That wasn't my
freaked-out scream.

14:17.022 --> 14:19.825
That was my "aliens are real and
that is so, so cool" scream.

14:19.892 --> 14:22.461
Tell me all about your unique
alien traits.

14:22.528 --> 14:25.164
- Well, I sleep with my eyes
open.

14:25.231 --> 14:26.198
- Really?

14:26.265 --> 14:28.400
- Sleep. Sleep. Sleep. Sleep.

14:28.467 --> 14:29.902
- Wake up!
- I'm awake!

14:29.969 --> 14:31.237
- What else do you do?

14:31.303 --> 14:33.439
- I also have this dope
fake-ifier belt

14:33.505 --> 14:35.608
that can turn me into whatever
I want

14:35.674 --> 14:40.179
so I can blend in with the crowd
all incognito-like.

14:40.246 --> 14:41.680
Check it!

14:41.747 --> 14:44.049
[warbling]

14:44.116 --> 14:47.786
I could be a rat with a banjo.

14:47.853 --> 14:53.125
The always stealthy toilet
with a moustache.

14:53.192 --> 14:54.326
[flushes]

14:54.393 --> 14:56.662
And my go-to,

14:56.729 --> 14:59.031
an old man juggling cats.

14:59.098 --> 15:01.867
[cats screeching]

15:01.934 --> 15:04.203
But!
Alas.

15:04.270 --> 15:07.306
It is bogus to have to disguise
myself.

15:07.373 --> 15:12.177
It would be so righteous to walk
amongst humans in my alien form

15:12.244 --> 15:14.046
and pursue my ultimate dream

15:14.113 --> 15:19.184
of styling hair under the
pseudonym Monsieur Pierre.

15:19.251 --> 15:20.386
[warbling]

15:25.291 --> 15:26.492
- Loving it!

15:26.558 --> 15:28.327
It's a W for Wanda.

15:28.394 --> 15:30.729
{\an1}- Hey, you know what else begins
with "W"?

15:30.796 --> 15:31.864
{\an1}Wrong!

15:31.930 --> 15:34.033
{\an1}And that's exactly
what Chloe was.

15:34.099 --> 15:36.535
- It's important that I was
wrong, Timmy.

15:36.602 --> 15:39.905
What is important is that Mark
is a very special boy,

15:39.972 --> 15:43.275
cat juggler, banjo rat,
creature,

15:43.342 --> 15:45.377
who should be able to be himself

15:45.444 --> 15:47.946
and follow his hairstyling
dream.

15:48.013 --> 15:51.583
- Alas, the world is not ready
for an alien squid

15:51.650 --> 15:53.385
named Mr. Pierre.

15:53.452 --> 15:55.354
{\an1}- Oh, Mark Chang,
you don't need to hide

15:55.421 --> 15:57.189
as a toilet with a moustache.

15:57.256 --> 15:59.158
{\an1}If people really got
to know you,

15:59.224 --> 16:00.526
they would love you.

16:00.592 --> 16:03.228
{\an3}- You have inspired me,
tiny dudette.

16:03.295 --> 16:05.898
{\an3}Accordingly,
I shall now reward you

16:05.964 --> 16:10.102
{\an3}with a complementary
hairdo-dette.

16:10.169 --> 16:12.304
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

16:12.371 --> 16:14.239
- Eeh!
I love it!

16:14.306 --> 16:15.541
Ooh.

16:15.607 --> 16:17.810
Although I may need
a neck brace.

16:17.876 --> 16:20.546
- I wonder where
Chloe Wrong-Michael is.

16:20.612 --> 16:24.350
Maybe she came down with a bad
case of Wrong-itis.

16:24.416 --> 16:26.285
- Did she catch it from you,
Turner?

16:26.352 --> 16:27.786
She better get here soon.

16:27.853 --> 16:29.621
If she doesn't give her report,

16:29.688 --> 16:32.157
then I'll actually have
to teach you bucket heads!

16:32.224 --> 16:33.792
- Fear not, Mr. Crocker,

16:33.859 --> 16:37.029
because I am here to present
a report of great import.

16:37.096 --> 16:39.898
I was originally going to posit
that aliens do not exist,

16:39.965 --> 16:43.769
but turns out I was--
oh, it's so hard to say this--

16:43.836 --> 16:45.337
wrong.

16:45.404 --> 16:46.805
[explosion and whistling]

16:46.872 --> 16:48.874
{\an1}- You've got some weird soup
in your thermos, Turner.

16:48.941 --> 16:52.578
- Instead I'm going to prove
that aliens do exist,

16:52.644 --> 16:55.547
with the help of my new friend,
Mark Chang,

16:55.614 --> 16:57.983
who happens to be a real-live
a--

16:58.050 --> 16:59.017
- No!

16:59.084 --> 17:00.018
Cosmo, Wanda--

17:00.085 --> 17:02.121
I wish time would stop!

17:02.187 --> 17:04.223
<i>[musical flourish]</i>

17:04.289 --> 17:05.391
[laughter]

17:05.457 --> 17:07.025
[pop]

17:07.092 --> 17:09.661
{\an3}Chloe, you can't tell anyone
that Mark's an alien.

17:09.728 --> 17:11.296
There are government agents
everywhere

17:11.363 --> 17:13.699
that'll snatch up Mark and study
him like a lab rat.

17:13.766 --> 17:16.335
- Timmy, it's important for Mark
to be himself,

17:16.402 --> 17:18.904
and I believe that people are
ready to embrace him

17:18.971 --> 17:20.539
in his true form.

17:20.606 --> 17:23.541
Also, there's not a government
agent within 500 miles of here.

17:23.608 --> 17:24.742
Cosmo, Wanda--

17:24.810 --> 17:26.345
I wish time would start again.

17:26.412 --> 17:28.881
<i>[fanfare]</i>

17:28.947 --> 17:30.082
[laughter]

17:30.149 --> 17:33.085
I give you my friend,
Mark Chang,

17:33.152 --> 17:35.187
a real, live alien.

17:35.254 --> 17:36.588
Do your thing, Mark.

17:36.655 --> 17:37.990
- Dudes and dudettes,

17:38.056 --> 17:39.758
behold: moi,

17:39.825 --> 17:44.763
as my most awesome self...

17:44.830 --> 17:45.898
Ah!

17:45.964 --> 17:47.599
[all scream]

17:47.666 --> 17:48.600
- [screams]

17:48.667 --> 17:49.968
- Let's get Mark out of here

17:50.035 --> 17:51.270
{\an3}before the government
agents show up.

17:51.336 --> 17:52.938
- Sorry, it's too late.

17:53.005 --> 17:55.941
We're already assembled,
and you're surrounded.

17:56.008 --> 17:57.776
[rip]

17:57.843 --> 18:00.012
- You're all government agents?

18:00.078 --> 18:01.346
Even you, Bucky?

18:01.413 --> 18:03.182
You can't even tie
your own shoes.

18:03.248 --> 18:04.583
- Hey, I don't have to.

18:04.650 --> 18:06.018
My mom got me clogs.

18:06.084 --> 18:09.455
They go clippity clop like
a horsey.

18:09.521 --> 18:10.823
- Bravo team leader,

18:10.889 --> 18:12.624
this is "Just Got My Braces
Tightened."

18:12.691 --> 18:14.660
We have an E.T.
What's your ETA?

18:14.726 --> 18:16.595
<i>- Foxy Cougar repelling in now.</i>

18:16.662 --> 18:18.931
<i>Don't look up;</i>
<i>I'm wearing a dress.</i>

18:18.997 --> 18:26.939
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:28.640 --> 18:34.980
[all scream]

18:35.047 --> 18:37.182
- So, mother, you're
a government agent?

18:37.249 --> 18:39.318
{\an1}That explains why you get picked
up for Bridge night

18:39.384 --> 18:40.719
by a Blackhawk helicopter.

18:40.786 --> 18:42.387
- You've seen too much, Denzil.

18:42.454 --> 18:44.556
I can either neutralize
your memory

18:44.623 --> 18:47.025
or deputize you
as a junior agent.

18:47.092 --> 18:49.194
- I could go either way.
It's your call.

18:49.261 --> 18:51.530
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:51.597 --> 18:53.532
Well, hello.
Who are you?

18:53.599 --> 18:55.467
Also, who am I?

18:55.534 --> 18:59.204
[all screaming]

18:59.271 --> 19:03.609
[all panting]

19:03.675 --> 19:05.511
- Walls made of books?

19:05.577 --> 19:07.980
[echoing]
What is this crazy place?

19:08.046 --> 19:09.815
- It's called "the library."

19:09.882 --> 19:12.251
You'd know that if you
ever studied.

19:12.317 --> 19:13.285
[pounding]

19:13.352 --> 19:15.521
{\an1}- We got to move.
[screams]

19:15.587 --> 19:21.026
[all screaming]

19:21.093 --> 19:23.428
Everyone, to my bicycle
built for two!

19:23.495 --> 19:26.698
It has an extra seat in case
a person in need wants a ride.

19:27.733 --> 19:28.867
[bell dings]

19:34.273 --> 19:35.407
[all scream]

19:35.474 --> 19:37.109
- Hello.
Who are you?

19:37.175 --> 19:38.277
Who am I?

19:38.343 --> 19:40.045
Where did I get this parachute?

19:40.112 --> 19:42.014
[all screaming]

19:42.080 --> 19:43.582
[poof]

19:43.649 --> 19:44.650
all: Whoo!

19:44.716 --> 19:46.251
- Full moon.

19:46.318 --> 19:48.487
Flying bike with an
extraterrestrial in a basket.

19:48.554 --> 19:50.856
I feel like I've seen this
before.

19:53.025 --> 19:55.961
- This is Foxy Cougar,
saying "land that bike."

19:56.028 --> 19:58.730
It's T-minus 5 minutes
to the early bird dinner

19:58.797 --> 20:00.299
at the Dimmsdale Diner,

20:00.365 --> 20:02.434
and they're having two kinds
of pudding.

20:02.501 --> 20:06.204
[all screaming]

20:06.271 --> 20:07.205
- Ooh!

20:07.272 --> 20:08.774
[siren blaring]

20:11.643 --> 20:13.045
- It's over, squid boy.

20:13.111 --> 20:14.846
Soon you'll be rooming in a cell

20:14.913 --> 20:18.150
next to the Loch Ness Monster
and Bigfoot.

20:18.216 --> 20:20.052
- Those are my dogs, yo!

20:20.118 --> 20:23.889
{\an3}Which explains why they did not
show for band practice.

20:23.956 --> 20:26.124
- Ooh, I'm normally opposed
to violence,

20:26.191 --> 20:29.127
but if you lay one hand on my
friend, Mark Chang...

20:29.194 --> 20:30.462
{\an1}Whoo-ah!

20:30.529 --> 20:31.463
{\an1}Ugh.

20:31.530 --> 20:32.698
- Just throw a net on them!

20:32.764 --> 20:34.800
The pudding's gonna get a skin.

20:37.502 --> 20:41.740
[all scream]

20:41.807 --> 20:44.443
[warbling]

20:44.509 --> 20:45.711
<i>- Measly earthlings.</i>

20:45.777 --> 20:47.212
<i>Beware: Mark Chang is a member</i>

20:47.279 --> 20:50.449
<i>of the intergalactic</i>
<i>alien federation</i>

20:50.515 --> 20:54.953
<i>and is therefore protected by</i>
<i>big scary aliens like me.</i>

20:55.020 --> 20:57.289
<i>Release him and the earth girl</i>
<i>at once,</i>

20:57.356 --> 21:00.025
<i>or your planet will be</i>
<i>vaporized--</i>

21:00.092 --> 21:01.026
<i>a lot!</i>

21:03.528 --> 21:05.297
[all scream]

21:05.364 --> 21:07.232
- Release the prisoners!

21:07.299 --> 21:08.233
[all scream]

21:09.901 --> 21:12.404
Okay, scary alien,
we did the thing.

21:12.471 --> 21:13.538
It's pudding time.

21:13.605 --> 21:15.107
<i>- Not so fast.</i>

21:15.173 --> 21:17.542
<i>We also demand that you allow</i>
<i>Mark Chang</i>

21:17.609 --> 21:21.446
<i>to live amongst you in his</i>
<i>alien form and style hair.</i>

21:21.513 --> 21:25.417
<i>In addition, you should totally</i>
<i>leave Chloe Carmichael alone,</i>

21:25.484 --> 21:27.552
<i>because she is awesome,</i>

21:27.619 --> 21:31.189
<i>even if she is wrong--</i>
<i>a lot.</i>

21:31.256 --> 21:35.160
- Finally, Timmy Turner must get
his own personal pizza chef.

21:35.227 --> 21:38.330
Ooh, and also he should never
have to go back

21:38.397 --> 21:41.667
to the scary room with the walls
made of books.

21:41.733 --> 21:44.236
- Oh, and release,
Nessie and Bigfoot.

21:44.302 --> 21:47.739
Our band's got a gig at a middle
school dance on Saturday.

21:47.806 --> 21:49.074
<i>- What Mark said.</i>

21:49.141 --> 21:50.208
- Done and done.

21:50.275 --> 21:51.209
Retreat!

22:00.686 --> 22:02.354
- Group hug, brahs!

22:02.421 --> 22:03.789
[laughs]

22:12.764 --> 22:14.833
- See, Timmy?
I was right after all.

22:14.900 --> 22:17.202
People did accept Mark Chang
for who he is,

22:17.269 --> 22:19.638
even if it did take the threat
of a global annihilation.

22:19.705 --> 22:22.441
- Yeah, and it's also cool
that I'm getting a haircut

22:22.507 --> 22:25.077
with the Loch Ness Monster
and Bigfoot!

22:25.143 --> 22:28.313
- Mr. Crocker, where are you?

22:28.380 --> 22:29.347
Who am I?

22:29.414 --> 22:30.348
{\an3}- Pudding!

22:30.415 --> 22:33.318
- I am Mr. Pierre!
